---

### üîå Circuit Connections

#### ‚û§ MQ135 to NodeMCU
| MQ135 Pin | NodeMCU Pin | Description           |
|-----------|-------------|-----------------------|
| VCC       | 3.3V        | Power supply          |
| GND       | GND         | Ground                |
| AO        | A0          | Analog output signal  |

#### ‚û§ Buzzer to NodeMCU
| Buzzer Pin | NodeMCU Pin | Description       |
|------------|-------------|-------------------|
| + (VCC)    | D1 (GPIO5)  | Buzzer input pin  |
| - (GND)    | GND         | Ground            |

> ‚ö†Ô∏è **Note**: The analog pin A0 on NodeMCU reads voltages between 0V and 1V. If your MQ135 outputs more than 1V, use a **voltage divider** (two resistors) to step down the voltage safely.

---

### üìã GPIO Reference for NodeMCU (ESP8266)

| NodeMCU Pin | GPIO No. | Usable For           |
|-------------|----------|----------------------|
| D0          | GPIO16   | General I/O          |
| D1          | GPIO5    | **Buzzer in this project** |
| D2          | GPIO4    | General I/O          |
| A0          | A0       | **MQ135 analog input** |

